Alright, since I am no longer active on this subnet - I will share the "Tegridy" update script:

``` 
#!/bin/bash

# Change to the workspace directory
cd /workspace/apps/templar || exit 1

# Get the current version/tag checked out
CURRENT_TAG=$(git describe --tags --abbrev=0)

# Fetch the latest release tag from GitHub
LATEST_TAG=$(curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/tplr-ai/templar/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name)

# Fallback if jq is not available:
# LATEST_TAG=$(curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/tplr-ai/templar/releases/latest | grep '"tag_name":' | sed -E 's/.*"([^"]+)".*/\1/')

if [[ ! "$LATEST_TAG" =~ ^v[0-9]+\.[0-9]+\.[0-9]+$ ]]; then
    echo "Error: LATEST_TAG '$LATEST_TAG' is not a valid semver tag. Aborting."
    exit 1
fi

# Check if the tags are different
if [ "$CURRENT_TAG" != "$LATEST_TAG" ]; then
    echo "New release detected: $LATEST_TAG. Proceeding with deployment..."

    # Fetch the latest tags
    git fetch --tags

    # Checkout the latest release tag
    git checkout tags/$LATEST_TAG -f

    # Stop all PM2 processes
    pm2 delete all

    # Clean up cache
    rm -rf /workspace/apps/templar/.cache/tplr/*

    # Activate virtual environment
    . /workspace/apps/templar/.venv/bin/activate

    # Update dependencies
    uv clean && uv sync --all-extras --prerelease=allow

    # Install PyTorch with CUDA support
    pip uninstall torch torchvision torchaudio -y
    # cuda 12.6 -> cu126 // cuda 12.8 -> cu128
    uv pip install torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu128
    python -c "import torch; print(torch.__version__); print(torch.version.cuda); print(torch.backends.cuda.is_built()); print(torch.cuda.is_available())"


    # Adjust configuration
    sed -i 's/"checkpoint_frequency": *[0-9]\+/"checkpoint_frequency": 1000000/' /workspace/apps/templar/*/hparams.json
    sed -i 's/timeout=*[0-9]\+/timeout=28/' /workspace/apps/templar/neurons/miner.py
    sed -i 's|if self.world_size < 4|if self.world_size < 128|g' /workspace/apps/templar/neurons/miner.py
    sed -i -E 's|weights_only=True|weights_only=False|g' /workspace/apps/templar/src/tplr/comms.py
    sed -i 's/^[[:space:]]*CPU_COUNT = .*/CPU_COUNT = 24/' /workspace/apps/templar/src/tplr/comms.py
    sed -i -e 's/dist.barrier(device_ids=\[self.rank\])/dist.barrier(device_ids=[torch.cuda.current_device()])/' /workspace/apps/templar/src/tplr/sharded_dataset.py

    # Clear history
    history -c

    # Run deployment scripts
    bash /workspace/pm2-logs
    bash /workspace/miner.sh

    echo "Deployment of release $LATEST_TAG complete."
else
    echo "Already running the latest release ($CURRENT_TAG). Skipping deployment."
fi
```
Cheers.
